dismissalText.commentary: Shoaib Malik run out (Williams) 3 (9b 0x4 0x6 14m) SR: 33.33

dismissalComment.html: Run out! Malik is gone.  Yousuf had come down the track for a lofted shot but was beaten in the flight and the inside edge saved him from getting stumped but the damage was done in the other end. The ball had rolled to short fine leg where Willams swooped on the ball and acted on the confusion between the batsmen and threw in a direct hit at the non-striker's end. The Pakistan captain is gone. He was late in getting back too; almost as if he didn't expect the throw to come in at his end.

dismissalText.commentary: Sean Williams c Shoaib Malik b Shahid Afridi 71 (101b 3x4 0x6 151m) SR: 70.29

dismissalComment.html: And William's defiant innings comes to an end. Floated on the middle stump and he whipped it straight to Malik at midwicket. He can't believe what he has done, hangs his head as he rests on the bat before slowly dragging himself of the ground.

dismissalText.commentary: Tatenda Taibu run out (Yasir Arafat/Kamran Akmal) 10 (20b 1x4 0x6 31m) SR: 50

dismissalComment.html: Full and outside off stump, Taibu square drove it to right of Arafat at wide third man but made the wrong decision to turn back for the second run. The throw was fast and accurate and at the base of the stumps. Akmal collected and broke the stumps in one clean motion and Taibu, despite his dive, couldn't make it in time.

headshotImage.longCaption: Sohail Tanvir player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: Pakistan have won. The last one has been wristed to fine leg boundary but Pakistan have wrapped up the series

commentPostTextItems.html: The players shake hands with each other, with the umpires, with the batsmen and Afridi is seen tugging Yousuf's beard. Both laugh and walk off, hands over the shoulder. The rest of the Zimbabwe squad come on to the ground and shake hands with Pakistan players. Afridi has been named the man of the match. And that's it from us. Good night and Shab Bakhair!

dismissalText.commentary: Salman Butt c Taylor b Chigumbura 23 (46b 3x4 0x6 54m) SR: 50

dismissalComment.html: And what a time to post that comment?! Butt is gone, flashing to backward point. It was a length delivery, outside off stump and Butt tried to make his own length and went for a slash but  it flew straight to the fielder. Zimbabwe have broken through.

dismissalText.commentary: Younis Khan lbw b Mupariwa 10 (10b 1x4 0x6 14m) SR: 100

dismissalComment.html: Strikes first ball. Caught dead plumb by the inswinger. It started to move in late from the off stump line and struck the front pad dead in front. Younis didn't expect the ball to come in the air and had pushed his front leg a touch across. Gone! Mupariwa, who dropped that catch, is singing the redemption song.

dismissalText.commentary: Nasir Jamshed c Chibhabha b Mupariwa 32 (49b 3x4 1x6 81m) SR: 65.3

dismissalComment.html: pulled straight to midwicket. It was a seam-up delivery, on the stumps and Nasir went for a pull, but only succeeded in sending it straight to the fielder

dismissalText.commentary: Shoaib Malik run out (Williams) 3 (9b 0x4 0x6 14m) SR: 33.33

dismissalComment.html: Run out! Malik is gone.  Yousuf had come down the track for a lofted shot but was beaten in the flight and the inside edge saved him from getting stumped but the damage was done in the other end. The ball had rolled to short fine leg where Willams swooped on the ball and acted on the confusion between the batsmen and threw in a direct hit at the non-striker's end. The Pakistan captain is gone. He was late in getting back too; almost as if he didn't expect the throw to come in at his end.

dismissalText.commentary: Mohammad Yousuf c & b Mupariwa 5 (26b 0x4 0x6 33m) SR: 19.23

dismissalComment.html: The pressure works! Yousuf is caught and bowled! Sharp catch too. It was fullish and Yousuf drives powerfully to the left of Mupariwa who holds on to it. 66 for 1 has turned into 78 for 5. Enter Shahid Afridi.

dismissalText.commentary: Shahid Afridi c Masakadza b Mupariwa 85 (52b 2x4 6x6 61m) SR: 163.46

dismissalComment.html: Afridi is gone. Big wicket. He walked across the stumps, went for a swipe across the line but got a thick edge over covers where Mazakadza ran behind to hold a neat catch

dismissalText.commentary: Misbah-ul-Haq c Chigumbura b Williams 44 (50b 3x4 1x6 85m) SR: 88

dismissalComment.html: And the reverse sweep goes awry this time. You can't win with that shot all the time. It was full and on the middle and leg, Misbah went for his reverse sweep but edged it straight to backward point.

dismissalText.commentary: Sean Williams c Shoaib Malik b Shahid Afridi 71 (101b 3x4 0x6 151m) SR: 70.29

dismissalComment.html: And William's defiant innings comes to an end. Floated on the middle stump and he whipped it straight to Malik at midwicket. He can't believe what he has done, hangs his head as he rests on the bat before slowly dragging himself of the ground.

dismissalText.commentary: Tatenda Taibu run out (Yasir Arafat/Kamran Akmal) 10 (20b 1x4 0x6 31m) SR: 50

dismissalComment.html: Full and outside off stump, Taibu square drove it to right of Arafat at wide third man but made the wrong decision to turn back for the second run. The throw was fast and accurate and at the base of the stumps. Akmal collected and broke the stumps in one clean motion and Taibu, despite his dive, couldn't make it in time.

stories.seoTitle: We lacked the killer instinct - Brown
